Your day-to-day assignments





The Quantitative Advisor will perform an independent review of business models under US and Canadian regulations, working closely with cross-functional teams including stakeholders, the model developer, model validators (Paris and New York offices), IT and auditors. Presentation of validation analysis to senior management is part of the job's responsibilities. He/she will have exposure to a variety of models used by the business and support functions, including models for credit risk, market risk, counterparty risk, stress testing, margins, IFRS9, trading algorithms and financial crime compliance.





Working with the Senior Quantitative Advisors and the Team Leader, the Quantitative Advisor will:






Perform independent review of relevant models that are employed at SG Americas at all stages of their lifecycle by:

Evaluating the conceptual soundness of models to ensure consistency of design by performing quantitative analysis and statistical testing, developing challenger models for benchmarking, reviewing model development processes, and challenging theoretical aspects by considering published research and industry practices ;

Work with large, complex datasets to verify quality and processing of input data (feed, transformation), accuracy of model results, and use advanced statistical techniques to work with sparse datasets;

Assess data quality and consistency between data characteristics and modeling assumptions;

Replicate and review model architecture to verify the accuracy of a model's calculations and ensure that the model is implemented as designed and that all components of the model function as intended.

Analyze model results through backtesting, benchmarking, sensitivity analysis using quantitative tools and techniques;

Review the ongoing monitoring of the model to ensure that it is performing as intended by assessing whether changes in products, exposures, activities, customers, or market conditions require adjustment, redevelopment, or replacement of the model. Verify model performance over time and ensure that model limitations are assessed;

Perform and interpret 2LOD model monitoring;

Evaluate model governance aspects such as model change management, ongoing monitoring and model risk assessment;

Assess overall model risk, report results, and propose remediation recommendations. Write comprehensive validation documents and prepare model review documents for MRM management and committees, RISQ management, and model and business partners ;

Maintain positive relationships and ongoing communication with model and business stakeholders;

Candidate must be able to verbally communicate the results of the model review (and interim feedback) - not just in the validation report (mentioned above);

Work with front office, model developers and risk managers for daily model review and corrective action tracking.


